<div id="InterceptArticle" style="display: none;">
  <article class="article-page page-width" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Article" style="padding-block:2.5rem var(--spacing-sections,64px); max-width:820px; margin:0 auto;">
    {% render 'breadcrumbs' %}
    <header class="article-page__header" style="margin-bottom:2rem; text-align:center;">
      <p class="text-eyebrow" id="ArticleCategoryDisplay" style="font-size:0.75rem; text-transform:uppercase; font-weight:700; color:var(--color-accent,#ff0000); letter-spacing:0.1em; margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Category</p>
      <h1 itemprop="headline" id="ArticleTitleDisplay" style="font-size:clamp(1.75rem,3vw,2.75rem); margin-bottom:1rem; color:#000000; font-weight:700;">Article Title</h1>
      <div class="article-page__meta" style="font-size:.875rem; color:#888; display:flex; gap:.5rem; justify-content:center;">
        <span>Tokiyo Lifestyle Editorial Team</span>
        <span>·</span>
        <time id="ArticleDateDisplay">July 15, 2026</time>
      </div>
    </header>
    <div class="article-page__image" style="border-radius:var(--card-radius,8px); overflow:hidden; margin-bottom:2.5rem; aspect-ratio:16/9; background:#000;">
      <img id="ArticleImageDisplay" src="" alt="" style="width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover;">
    </div>
    <div class="article-page__body rte" itemprop="articleBody" id="ArticleBodyDisplay" style="line-height:1.8; color:#333; font-size:1.05rem; text-align:left;">
      <!-- Article Content will be dynamically inserted here -->
    </div>
  </article>
</div>

<script>
  (function() {
    const handleRoute = () => {
      const path = window.location.pathname.toLowerCase();
      const def404 = document.getElementById('Default404');
      const about = document.getElementById('InterceptAbout');
      const b2b = document.getElementById('InterceptB2B');
      const careers = document.getElementById('InterceptCareers');
      const franchise = document.getElementById('InterceptFranchise');
      const wishlist = document.getElementById('InterceptWishlist');
      
      const articles = {
        'why-fabric-quality-matters': {
          title: "Why Fabric Quality Matters: Cotton vs Cotton Blend",
          category: "Fabric & Quality",
          date: "July 15, 2026",
          image: "{{ 'hero-slide-3.png' | asset_url }}",
          body: `
            <p>Streetwear isn't just about graphics; it's about structure, drape, and longevity. The fabric you wear defines how the design moves, how it breathes, and how it holds up after wash cycles.</p>
            <h2 style="font-size: 1.75rem; margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: #000000; font-weight:700;">The Weight of Style: Why 240 GSM Matters</h2>
            <p>GSM (Grams per Square Meter) is the metric standard for fabric weight. Ordinary tees fall between 140-180 GSM. Streetwear requires heavy draping, which is why Tokiyo Lifestyle uses premium 240 GSM combed cotton. This ensures a thick, boxy drape that resists creasing and retains its premium silhouette throughout the day.</p>
            <blockquote style="border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent, #ff0000); padding-left: 1.5rem; margin: 1.5rem 0; font-style: italic; color: #555;">"The fabric determines the silhouette. An oversized tee in thin fabric clings; in 240 GSM cotton, it drapes."</blockquote>
            <h2 style="font-size: 1.75rem; margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: #000000; font-weight:700;">Cotton vs Cotton Blends: The Pure Advantage</h2>
            <p>While poly-blends are cheaper to produce, pure combed cotton offers unparalleled breathability and comfort. Cotton fibers are combed to remove short fibers and impurities, resulting in a super-soft, durable surface that is perfect for DTF (Direct to Film) and puff printing. Cotton blends often trap heat and develop lint (pilling) over time, losing that clean look.</p>
            <p>At Tokiyo, our commitment is simple: 100% premium super-combed cotton, processed with bio-wash for ultimate softness, making it the perfect choice for everyday wear in all seasons.</p>
          `
        },
        'how-to-choose-the-perfect-oversized-fit': {
          title: "How to Choose the Perfect Oversized Fit: A Streetwear Guide",
          category: "Buying Guides",
          date: "July 14, 2026",
          image: "{{ 'hero-slide-2.png' | asset_url }}",
          body: `
            <p>The term "oversized" is often misunderstood. Many believe it simply means buying two sizes larger than usual. However, buying standard-cut shirts in larger sizes results in long hemlines and loose collars, rather than a clean streetwear aesthetic.</p>
            <h2 style="font-size: 1.75rem; margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: #000000; font-weight:700;">The Anatomy of a Streetwear Fit</h2>
            <p>A true oversized tee is engineered from the ground up:
              <ul style="margin-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; list-style-type: disc;">
                <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Drop-Shoulder Seams:</strong> The shoulder seams are designed to sit lower, creating a relaxed, boxy feel without excess bulk.</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Boxy Silhouette:</strong> The chest and waist widths are increased while keeping the length balanced, so the shirt doesn't look like a dress.</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Snug Ribbed Collar:</strong> Even with a wider body, the collar is kept snug to frame the neck properly and prevent a sloppy look.</li>
              </ul>
            </p>
            <h2 style="font-size: 1.75rem; margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: #000000; font-weight:700;">Finding Your Perfect Size</h2>
            <p>For a standard, premium oversized look, we recommend ordering your true size. Our patterns are designed to naturally sit drop-shoulder and boxy. If you prefer an extra-exaggerated drape, size up once. If you prefer a slightly trimmer fit that still maintains the streetwear aesthetic, size down once.</p>
          `
        },
        'how-to-wash-printed-t-shirts': {
          title: "How to Wash Printed T-Shirts and Prevent Fading",
          category: "Care Guides",
          date: "July 12, 2026",
          image: "{{ 'hero-slide-1.png' | asset_url }}",
          body: `
            <p>You've invested in premium graphic streetwear. To ensure your prints remain vibrant and crack-free, proper laundering care is essential. Follow our laundry guide to keep your wardrobe looking fresh.</p>
            <h2 style="font-size: 1.75rem; margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: #000000; font-weight:700;">The Golden Rules of Graphic Tee Care</h2>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;"><strong>1. Turn it Inside Out:</strong> Always turn your garments inside out before placing them in the washing machine. This protects the print surface from friction against other clothes.</p>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;"><strong>2. Use Cold Water:</strong> Warm water can loosen the adhesive bonds of prints and cause cotton fibers to shrink. Always wash in cold water (30°C or below).</p>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;"><strong>3. Mild Detergent Only:</strong> Avoid bleach or harsh chemical fabric softeners. Use a mild liquid detergent to clean gently.</p>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;"><strong>4. Air Dry (Never Tumble Dry):</strong> Heat is the ultimate enemy of prints. Tumble dryers cause graphic cracking and shrinkage. Instead, dry your shirts flat or hang them in the shade.</p>
            <blockquote style="border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent, #ff0000); padding-left: 1.5rem; margin: 1.5rem 0; font-style: italic; color: #555;">"Proper care preserves both print and fabric. A well-cared-for Tokiyo tee can last for years without fading."</blockquote>
          `
        },
        'streetwear-trends-in-india': {
          title: "Streetwear Trends in India: Street Culture & Devotion Within",
          category: "Fashion & Styling",
          date: "July 10, 2026",
          image: "{{ 'hero-slide-4.png' | asset_url }}",
          body: `
            <p>India is undergoing a massive style transition. Streetwear has evolved from a niche global import into a full-fledged cultural movement, mixing local values, anime devotion, and bold styling.</p>
            <h2 style="font-size: 1.75rem; margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: #000000; font-weight:700;">The Fusion of Indian Art and Global Aesthetics</h2>
            <p>Modern Indian streetwear designers are blending traditional icons and devotions with heavy boxy fits. Graphics featuring regional typography, mythic designs, and urban scenes are resonating with a generation that wants to wear their roots proudly.</p>
            <h2 style="font-size: 1.75rem; margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: #000000; font-weight:700;">Anime Culture Meets Premium Apparel</h2>
            <p>Anime is no longer a subculture; it's a mainstream phenomenon. Graphic prints featuring iconic anime characters, streetwear-adapted color blocks, and epic quotes are now the most sought-after drops. The key to styling them is pairing them with solid cargo pants and sneakers, letting the heavy graphic tee stand as the center of the outfit.</p>
            <p>At Tokiyo Lifestyle, we are at the center of this movement — creating premium streetwear that respects quality and speaks to the bold, creative soul of modern India.</p>
          `
        }
      };

      const articleMatch = Object.keys(articles).find(key => path.includes(key));
      if (articleMatch) {
        const article = articles[articleMatch];
        if (def404) def404.style.display = 'none';
        if (interceptArticle) {
          interceptArticle.style.display = 'block';
          document.getElementById('ArticleCategoryDisplay').innerText = article.category;
          document.getElementById('ArticleTitleDisplay').innerText = article.title;
          document.getElementById('ArticleDateDisplay').innerText = article.date;
          document.getElementById('ArticleImageDisplay').src = article.image;
          document.getElementById('ArticleImageDisplay').alt = article.title;
          document.getElementById('ArticleBodyDisplay').innerHTML = article.body;
        }
        document.title = article.title + " | Tokiyo Lifestyle";
        return;
      }

      if (path.includes('about')) {
        if (def404) def404.style.display = 'none';
        if (about) about.style.display = 'block';
        document.title = "About Us | Tokiyo Lifestyle";
      } else if (path.includes('bulk-order') || path.includes('b2b')) {
        if (def404) def404.style.display = 'none';
        if (b2b) b2b.style.display = 'block';
        document.title = "Bulk Order & B2B | Tokiyo Lifestyle";
      } else if (path.includes('career')) {
        if (def404) def404.style.display = 'none';
        if (careers) careers.style.display = 'block';
        document.title = "Careers | Tokiyo Lifestyle";
      } else if (path.includes('franchise')) {
        if (def404) def404.style.display = 'none';
        if (franchise) franchise.style.display = 'block';
        document.title = "Franchise Partnership | Tokiyo Lifestyle";
      } else if (path.includes('wishlist')) {
        if (def404) def404.style.display = 'none';
        if (wishlist) wishlist.style.display = 'block';
        document.title = "My Wishlist | Tokiyo Lifestyle";
        
        // Render wishlist products using standard function if wishlist.js is loaded
        const grid = document.querySelector('[data-wishlist-grid]');
        if (grid && typeof renderWishlistPage === 'function') {
          renderWishlistPage(grid);
        }
      }
    };

    if (document.readyState === 'loading') {
      document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', handleRoute);
    } else {
      handleRoute();
    }
  })();
</script>

<style>
  /* 404 styles */
  .error-page { text-align:center; padding:6rem 1rem; }
  .error-page__code { font-size:8rem; font-weight:800; color:#e1dbd4; line-height:1; margin-bottom:0; font-family:var(--font-heading,'Poppins',sans-serif); }
  .error-page__content h1 { font-size:2rem; margin-bottom:1rem; }
  .error-page__content p { color:#888; margin-bottom:2rem; }

  /* About page styles */
  .about-page { padding-block: 3.5rem 5rem; background: var(--color-background, #FFFFFF); }
  .about-page__hero { text-align: center; max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto 4rem; }
  .about-page__hero h1 { font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3.25rem); margin: 0.5rem 0 1.5rem; font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: -0.02em; }
  .about-page__lead { font-size: 1.125rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--color-text-muted, #767674); }
